================================================================
Derivation from MMDVMHost (by Jonathan Naylor, G4KLX)
https://github.com/g4klx/MMDVMHost
================================================================

Affected files (in this crate):
    src/lib.rs
    src/tokio_shell/modem_loop.rs
    src/tokio_shell/tx_queue.rs

These modules mirror the periodic-GetStatus poll cadence, the per-mode
TX ring buffers, and the space-gated drain logic described in the
upstream file:

    ref/MMDVMHost/Modem.cpp

Specifically mirrored regions (see the //! doc comments in each file
for exact line references):
    - m_statusTimer cadence (Modem.cpp:245)
    - m_playoutTimer cadence (Modem.cpp:247)
    - Per-mode m_tx<MODE>Data ring buffers (Modem.cpp:288-315)
    - Space-gated drain logic (Modem.cpp:1049-1220)
    - D-STAR slot-cost constants (Modem.cpp:1053-1055)

Copyright (c) 2015-2026 Jonathan Naylor, G4KLX
    (https://github.com/g4klx)

Modem.cpp carries the GPL-2.0-or-later header ("either version 2 of
the License, or (at your option) any later version"). This crate
therefore inherits the "or later" grant.

No code from MMDVMHost is copied verbatim into this crate. The
derivation is documented inline in each affected module via
"//! Mirrors ref/MMDVMHost/Modem.cpp:<line>" comments; those pointers
are the audit trail, not copy-paste. The Rust implementations use
tokio channels, VecDeque, and tokio::time::Interval in place of the
upstream CThread / CRingBuffer / CTimer primitives.

